@NODE USE "Usage"
PromoteView can be started from CLI only. Its argument template is:

       SCREENMODE/A,XPOS/N,YPOS/N,INSTALL/S


SCREENMODE is a hexadecimal screenmode-ID number, like one of these:

         39024     for Multiscan monitor
         69024     for Euro72 monitor
         99004     for DblNTSC monitor
         a9004     for DblPAL monitor

Once started it installs its patch and waits till you press CTRL-C.
After you have done so, it removes its patch and ends.
If you give the INSTALL argument, it installs its patch and ends
immediately. In this case you can only remove the patch by resetting
your computer.

Examples:

    PromoteView 39024
    PromoteView 99024 install
    PromoteView screenmode=a9024

Note that there is no errormessage if something fails. PromoteView
will simply end without installing the patch.

There might be small memory loss if using old OS1.3 programs like
Movieplayer. Sorry, I found no way around it.

If PromoteView forces a new screen mode, it centers the visible area
in the upper left of the screen. This should be visible on most VGA
monitors. If you do not like it, you can play around with the XPOS and
YPOS integer values (XPOS: Number of quad-pixels).

Example:

    PromoteView a9024 10 17

This moves the visible area 40 pixels right and 17 pixels down.



The hint of the day:
I have added these Tooltypes to the Multiscan monitor icon and
adjusted the Overscan preferences. Now I have a 640x480 pixels
display running at 63Hz.

  TOTROWS=0x1fc
  TOTCLKS=0x6f
  HBSTRT=0x01
  HBSTOP=0x21
  VBSTRT=0x00
  VBSTOP=0xccd
@ENDNODE

@NODE HIST "History"
V1: Initial release.
    It was called VGApatch and by accident it was stored in util/shell
    in Aminet.

V2: Changed name to PromoteView. (I did not like "VGApatch" anymore)
    Fixed bug in hexadecimal number analyzing thanks to Marek Jablonski.
    Fixed problems with SetFunction managers thanks to Gunther Nikl.
    Added ReadArgs CLI interface.
    Added INSTALL switch.

V3: Fixed bug with HAM, ExtraHalfBright and DualPlayfield modes thanks
    to Daniel J. O'Connor.
    Added XPOS and YPOS keywords.
    Maybe this is the last release.
@ENDNODE

@NODE AUTO "Author"
Though this is a quite small program, I have spent lots of time in it,
because I had to find out how to make it work. Since this View stuff
of graphics.library is not well documented, this was a quite hard job.

